	<Container>
		<section class="maintenance-section">
			<h2>Maintenance Guidelines</h2>
			<p class="section-intro">
				Proper maintenance ensures your garage floor epoxy coating maintains its appearance and performance for decades.
			</p>
			
			<div class="maintenance-content">
				<div class="maintenance-do">
					<h3>Daily Care Instructions</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Immediate Spill Cleanup:</strong> Clean automotive fluids, chemicals, and spills immediately to prevent any potential staining</li>
						<li><strong>Regular Sweeping:</strong> Remove dirt, debris, and road salt with a soft-bristle broom or microfiber dust mop</li>
						<li><strong>Weekly Mopping:</strong> Use warm water with mild detergent for routine cleaning. Avoid abrasive cleaners</li>
						<li><strong>Mat Usage:</strong> Place mats under vehicles during winter to catch road salt and prevent tracking throughout the garage</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="maintenance-dont">
					<h3>Long-Term Maintenance</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Annual Deep Cleaning:</strong> Thorough cleaning with degreasing agents to remove accumulated grime</li>
						<li><strong>Inspection Schedule:</strong> Annual inspection for any wear patterns, minor damage, or areas needing attention</li>
						<li><strong>Minor Repairs:</strong> Small chips or scratches can be spot-repaired to prevent further damage</li>
						<li><strong>Protective Measures:</strong> Use furniture pads under heavy equipment and avoid dragging sharp objects</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="maintenance-avoid">
